<i>noun</i>: 염소, 鹽素 <br>
<ul>
<li>
<i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>염소, 鹽素</dt><br>
<dd>a common nonmetallic element belonging to the halogens; best known as a heavy yellow irritating toxic gas; used to purify water and as a bleaching agent and disinfectant; occurs naturally only as a salt (as in sea water)</dd><br>
<dd><i>synonyms</i>: chlorine, Cl, atomic number 17, E925 when used as a food additive</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>
